text.text:
Hers's the battle for social media supremacy is heating up. Threads, an Instagram app by Meta is a new app that could challenge Twitter's dominance.

Over 10 Millions people sign up for Threads within 7 hours of Launch which is actually a clear threat for Elon Musk's Twitter.

Threads plans to be a part of the fediverse. The fediverse is a decentralized social media network that is more private and secure than traditional social media platforms. This means that you will be able to use Threads to connect with people who are using other fediverse platforms, such as Mastodon and GNU Social. There is no single point of failure that if one server goes down, your data will still be accessible on other servers.

I'm also on Threads as @hassanmatloob1.0. Install the app to follow my threads and replies. https://lnkd.in/d88S7KQM

 #socialmedia #network #threads #twitter

text.text: Hassan Matloob reposted this

Your physical and mental health is your most important asset. Find an employer who thinks the exact same thing, it’s no less than you deserve.

If you are working on your well-being but your workplace is a toxic environment you will find it hard to fully recover from its damage no matter how much effort you put into your well-being.

Have the confidence when interviewing for a role, to "interview" the company.  Ask them about their culture and how they have the mental well-being of staff as a key concern.  If they don't it’s the first sign of a potential toxic environment.

Some other signs are:

1. There are toxic leaders across the organisation 
2. Company culture does not match stated values.
3. Star performers who damage other staff are still rewarded
4. There is a blame culture that forces defensive behaviour in all
5. Leadership does nothing about damaging behaviour 
6. Talent and ambition is viewed as a threat

 #mentalhealth #leadership #career #success #motivation #valueyourself #humanresources #personaldevelopment #whatinspiresme #wellbeing

text.text:
🎃 A Spine-tingling Afternoon of AI Horror! 🤖

I had the absolute pleasure of attending the #AIHalloween Event organized by Women Techmakers Lahore which #RoadToDevfest. It was an exceptional gathering where innovation and imagination merged seamlessly.  

We delved deep into those eerie AI flicks like 'M3gan' & 'Joan is Awful' 🤖🎬 while covering Google AI Tools: Palm API, Keras, Tensorflow, and more for Responsible AI development.

Heartfelt thanks to the Google wizards, Eric ShangKuan and Huzaifa Habib  and to Google Developer Experts - Eric Bhatti, Sakina Abbas, who shed light on Flutter and Firebase. And, of course, kudos to our AI game changers - Maria Hussain, Haleema Tallat and Fariha Muazzam, as well as the amazing team of Alethea AI. 

A massive shoutout to the event management team led by Minahil Kaleem, Iqra Hameed, Ramsha Siddiqui and all others who made this day truly enchanting.

Now, I'm eagerly looking forward to more magical moments at Devfest.

#AIHalloween #WomenTechMarkers #RoadToDevfest #WomenInTech #GoogleDevfest #TechMagic
